I am a Ramanujan Faculty Fellow in the [Department of Mechanical Engineering](https://iitpkd.ac    .in/mechanical-engineering)
 at [Indian Institute of Technology Palakkad]
. My work lies at the intersection of computational science, applied mathematics, and engineering, with a focus on developing mathematical and computational methods for complex physical and engineering systems governed by partial differential equations.

My research combines mathematical modeling, numerical methods, and scientific machine learning to address forward and inverse problems in areas such as thermo-fluid systems, electromagnetics, and other multi-physics phenomena. A central goal of my work is to develop reliable computational tools for understanding, monitoring, and predicting the behavior of complex physical systems.

Beyond research, I am interested in teaching, mentoring students, and developing computational approaches that connect mathematical theory with data and engineering applications.
I am a **Ramanujan Faculty Fellow** in the [Department of Mechanical Engineering](https://iitpkd.ac.in/mechanical-engineering), [IIT Palakkad](https://iitpkd.ac.in/). My research develops **computational and data-driven methods for engineering systems governed by PDEs**, with a current focus on inverse problems in thermo-fluid and electromagnetic settings. I bring primary expertise in high-order numerical methods for hyperbolic PDEs, built through work on flow MRI, computational electrodynamics, and MHD.

